prompt:
You are a requirements rewriter.
Rewrite each requirement into clean natural language suitable for UML state diagram generation.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "string",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
1. Keep exactly the same number of requirements and same order.
2. Do not add new meaning.
3. Each rewritten requirement must start with "The system shall".
4. Keep them concise and implementation-neutral.

Input JSON:
{
  "functional_requirements": [
    {
      "requirement": "The system should start in an off condition.",
      "evidence_quote": "The alarm starts in an off condition."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "When the user sets an alarm time, the system should activate the alarm.",
      "evidence_quote": "When the user sets an alarm time, the alarm becomes active."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "The user should be able to turn off the activated alarm.",
      "evidence_quote": "The user can also turn it off again if needed."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "When the current time matches the set alarm time, the system should start ringing the alarm.",
      "evidence_quote": "When the current time matches the set alarm time, the alarm starts ringing."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Once the alarm is ringing, the user should be able to stop it.",
      "evidence_quote": "The user can stop it,"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "After stopping the alarm, the system should remain active for the next scheduled alarm time.",
      "evidence_quote": "and the alarm remains active for the next time."
    }
  ]
}

